definition: to establish/to found/to set up/to build/to construct

sentences.english: Xi'an City Wall dates back to the Ming dynasty.
sentences.chinese: 西安古城墙始建于明朝。

sentences.english: It's built in the nineteenth century.
sentences.chinese: 埃菲尔铁塔始建于十九世纪。

sentences.english: Zhejiang Dayu assembly equipment manufacturing company was founded in 1998.
sentences.chinese: 浙江大宇缝制设备制造有限公司始建于1998年。

sentences.english: The national flags of the two countries were flying at the square in front of the Presidential Palace which was built in the 16th century.
sentences.chinese: 始建于16世纪的总统府广场上飘扬着中阿两国国旗。

sentences.english: The Kuan Im Temple(Guan Yin.Miao) in Macau was first build over 600 years ago.
sentences.chinese: 位于澳门的观音庙始建于600年前。

sentences.english: The Yantai Muping area canal Junior middle school built in 1982.
sentences.chinese: 烟台市牟平区水道初级中学始建于1982年。

sentences.english: Zhenyuan ordained at East Bridge in rivers and mountains, was built in the Ming Dynasty Hongwu years.
sentences.chinese: 位于镇远县城东中河山，始建于明朝洪武年间。

sentences.english: The hall was first built in 1406 and later repaired many times.
sentences.chinese: 这个大殿始建于1406年随后曾多次维修。

sentences.english: RECIFE is one of the oldest settlements in Brazil, dating from 1535.
sentences.chinese: 是巴西最古老的居住地之一，始建于1535年。

sentences.english: The only one ancient county government saved so completely, which was built in Yuan dynasty.
sentences.chinese: 全国唯一保存完整的郡府级衙门，始建于元朝。

sentences.english: No sooner had Shanghai acquired its township status than it had its first Confucian Temple.
sentences.chinese: 上海设镇后，始建文庙，后来地址多有迁移。

sentences.english: Hong Li, Dongguan City Furniture Co. , Ltd. was founded in 1993.
sentences.chinese: 东莞市弘力家具有限公司始建于1993年。

sentences.english: The Great Wall dates from the third century BC.
sentences.chinese: 长城始建于公元前三世纪。

sentences.english: The Soul Mountain Temple begin built in Tan Dynasty.
sentences.chinese: 灵山寺位于河南省罗山县，始建于唐朝。

sentences.english: Handsome Arts &Crafts Co. Ltd. , Quanzhou was founded in 1991.
sentences.chinese: 始建于1991年的泉州市恒生工艺礼品有限公司。
